High levels of IgG4 to Schistosoma mansoni egg antigens in individuals with periportal fibrosis. Specific IgG4 and IgE responses to adult worm antigen and soluble egg antigen (SEA) were examined in 267 individuals from an area in which schistosomiasis mansoni is endemic. Based on information obtained from clinical and sonographic examinations of this sample, the individuals were divided in three groups: 1) 204 individuals without periportal fibrosis, and liver and spleen enlargements 2) 41 individuals without periportal fibrosis, but presenting with organopathy, with or without organomegaly